  "prompt": "What happens when a batsman hit a shot and ball hits the spidercam?",
  "response": "When a batsman hits the ball and it strikes the Spidercam during a cricket match, the rules of the game come into play to determine the outcome. Typically, if the ball hits the Spidercam and is not considered to have made contact with the ground, the ball is declared dead. \n\nThe umpire will call for a dead ball, and the delivery will not count. The batting team will not be credited with any runs from that delivery, and the batsman will not be out. The ball is then reset for the next delivery. \n\nThe Spidercam, which is a cable-suspended camera used for capturing aerial shots, is considered part of the playing area, but any contact with it does not change the fundamental ruling; the ball is simply dead at that point.",
